    <text>
        <body>
            <div xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Ferenc Újlaki (Augsburg, 1 November 1530)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1"> A desire to dominate has overcome their common friend,
                            Oláh feels ashamed for him. He is hurting everyone, especially in
                            conversation, and Oláh cannot but be surprised at this. Oláh is writing
                            to let Újlaki know what an inglorious life this friend of theirs is
                            living.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/C8601DD5-3453-4805-9760-70A97277B6AA
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Ad <persName>Franciscum Wilaky</persName> praepositum
                    Posoniensem.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Cum scias ex veteri proverbio <quote xml:id="quote.1">neminem bene
                        imperare</quote><note type="quote" xml:id="note.quote.1">Cf. Erasm. <hi
                            rend="italic">Adag.</hi> I,I,3: “Nemo bene imperat, nisi qui paruerit
                        imperio”, see <hi rend="smallcap">Mynors</hi> 1982, 50–51.</note>, nisi
                    prius paruerit imperio, non possum satis mirari de homine illo, quem scis
                    utriusque nostrum amicum, qui imperare velit, nunquam prius accepto imperio.
                    Tanta illius temeritas et impudens audacia, ut nihil non audeat; pudet me facti
                    illius, quod sine ulla verecundia et humanitatis ratione assidue facit, nullum
                    habet cum veneranda verecundia commercium. Ita omnia emendicat et palpat
                    quemlibet stolidis potius quam modestis verbis, ut mirareris de ipsius
                    stultitia, si quando eius facta videres. Haec volui tibi nota facere, ut scires,
                    quam hic non laudabilem agat vitam. Omnino futurum opinor esse necessarium, ut
                    aliqua ars quaeratur, quae hominem ab hac impudentia deterreat, et ut dicunt
                        <quote xml:id="quote.2">quaerendum esse malum cuneum, quo malus cuneus
                        extrudatur</quote><note type="quote" xml:id="note.quote.2">Cf. Erasm. <hi
                            rend="italic">Adag.</hi> I,II,5: “Malo nodo, malus quaerendus cuneus”,
                        see <hi rend="smallcap">Mynors</hi> 1982, 149–150, and Jerome, <hi
                            rend="italic">Ep.</hi> 69,4: “Iuxta vulgare proverbium: malo arboris
                        nodo malus cuneus requirendus est.” See also <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Ijsewijn–Sacré–Tournoy</hi> 1993, 14.</note>. Vale et scribe ad me
                    saepius quam hactenus.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Ex <placeName>Augusta</placeName> prima Novembris MDXXX.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
